This is a 78-year-old gentleman presenting for the below concerns:
#1 Probable rectal cancer
Even though the colonoscopy report suggests this is one localized to the anus, given the histology being adenocarcinoma this is most likely consistent with rectal adenocarcinoma.  We will recommend the following:
1.  Review outside pathology and CT-scan.
2.  We will perform an endorectal ultrasound for further staging purposes.
3.  Routine labs and EKG.
4.  We will have him return to meet with us and Surgery once these tests are complete.
ADVANCE DIRECTIVES
Advance directive or living will: Yes, not on file at PVCC.

